    "body": "### Problem\n\nThere's some weird scenario in which two `<C-s>` keypresses are needed to make the signature help popup appear.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nI've narrowed the issue down to the following repro case.\n```\ncat >/tmp/repro.lua <<HERE\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"CursorMoved\", {\n  callback = function() end,\n})\nvim.keymap.set(\"i\", \"<C-s>\", function()\n  vim.lsp.util.open_floating_preview({ \"line1\", \"line2\", }, \"markdown\", {})\nend)\nHERE\nnvim --clean --cmd 'let g:loaded_matchparen = 1'  -c 'so /tmp/repro.lua'\n```\nand then in insert mode:\n```\ntest<C-s><C-s>\n```\nDoing any of the following will allow a single <C-s> to trigger the preview window:\n- Not setting `loaded_matchparen`\n- Removing the empty `CursorMoved` autocmd\n- Entering insert mode via \"i\" and then pressing `<C-s>`. Entering via \"a\" requires two presses.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo situation requires `<C-s>` to be pressed twice.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.3.2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.41.1 (also tested in regular terminal app)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
